<p>This is similar to the question asked in this post:<a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/10856216/how-do-you-make-a-handlebars-helper-that-is-aware-of-ember-bindings">How do you make a Handlebars helper that is aware of Ember bindings?</a></p>  <p>I want my customized Handlebars block helper to be aware of Ember bindings:</p>  <pre><code>{{#myHelper my.binding}}     show something here {{/myHelper}} </code></pre>  <p>But the helper receives <code>my.binding</code> as string instead of the value. How do I pass the value into the helper?</p>